Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.61,1:23:15.57,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎一定要符合经济奖励\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}has to realign the financial incentives.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.07,1:23:18.78,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这些公司没有需要改变的财政理由\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}There's no fiscal reason for these companies to change.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.86,1:23:21.32,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎所以我才认为 我们需要监管\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And that is why I think we need regulation.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.41,1:23:24.29,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎手机公司有无数的关于你的敏感数据\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The phone company has tons of sensitive data about you,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.37,1:23:27.54,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们有很多法律去保证 ‎他们不会利用这些数据做错事\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}and we have a lot of laws that make sure they don't do the wrong things.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.62,1:23:31.50,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎在数码隐私上 我们几乎没有立法\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We have almost no laws around digital privacy, for example.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.58,1:23:34.42,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们可以对数据收集和处理收税\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We could tax data collection and processing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.50,1:23:37.55,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎原理等同于你交水费\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}the same way that you, for example, pay your water bill{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.63,1:23:39.72,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎监控你自己的用水量\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}by monitoring the amount of water that you use.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.80,1:23:43.22,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎让这些公司因为持有的数据资产交税\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You tax these companies on the data assets that they have.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.30,1:23:44.76,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎就能给他们一个财政理由\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It gives them a fiscal reason{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.85,1:23:47.85,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎不去获取地球上每一条数据\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}to not acquire every piece of data on the planet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.93,1:23:50.56,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎立法在这方面太落后了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The law runs way behind on these things,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.65,1:23:55.86,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎但据我所知 当前状况的存在 ‎不是为了保护用户\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}but what I know is the current situation exists not for the protection of users,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.94,1:23:58.70,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎而是为了保护这些巨型的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}but for the protection of the rights and privileges{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.78,1:24:01.45,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎超级富有公司的权利和特权\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}of these gigantic, incredibly wealthy companies.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.24,1:24:05.83,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们要一直听从最有钱 ‎最有权力的人吗？\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Are we always gonna defer to the richest, most powerful people?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.91,1:24:07.41,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎还是我们要说\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Or are we ever gonna say,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.95,1:24:12.04,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎“有时候 确实是有国家利益\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}"You know, there are times when there is a national interest.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.13,1:24:15.59,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎有时候 人民的利益 用户利益\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}There are times when the interests of people, of users,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.67,1:24:17.38,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎其实比一个\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}is actually more important{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.01,1:24:21.47,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎已经是亿万富翁的人的利益 ‎更加重要？”\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}than the profits of somebody who's already a billionaire"?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.89,1:24:26.60,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这些市场削弱了民主 削弱了自由\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}These markets undermine democracy, and they undermine freedom,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.68,1:24:28.52,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎应该对他们进行法律的制裁\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}and they should be outlawed.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.14,1:24:31.81,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这不是激进的提议\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}This is not a radical proposal.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.90,1:24:34.19,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们有法律制裁的其他市场\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}There are other markets that we outlaw.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.27,1:24:36.98,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们制裁人类器官贩卖市场\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We outlaw markets in human organs.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.07,1:24:39.49,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们制裁人类奴隶市场\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We outlaw markets in human slaves.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.94,1:24:44.03,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎因为它们都有不可避免的破坏性后果\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Because they have inevitable destructive consequences.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.53,1:24:45.83,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们生活的世界\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We live in a world{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.91,1:24:50.00,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎死去的树比活着的树更有经济价值\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}in which a tree is worth more, financially, dead than alive,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.08,1:24:53.83,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这个世界 死去的鲸 ‎比活着的鲸更有价值\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}in a world in which a whale is worth more dead than alive.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.92,1:24:56.34,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎只要我们的经济这样运转\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}For so long as our economy works in that way{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.42,1:24:58.13,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎公司不受监管\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}and corporations go unregulated,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.21,1:25:00.67,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎它们就会继续破坏树木\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}they're going to continue to destroy trees,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.76,1:25:01.76,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎继续捕杀鲸\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}to kill whales,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.84,1:25:06.10,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎在地球上挖矿 从地下抽石油\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}to mine the earth, and to continue to pull oil out of the ground,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.18,1:25:08.39,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎虽然我们知道 这样做会破坏地球\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}even though we know it is destroying the planet{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.47,1:25:12.14,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们知道 这样做会为未来几代人 ‎留下一个更不堪的世界\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}and we know that it's going to leave a worse world for future generations.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.23,1:25:13.85,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这是目光短浅\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}This is short-term thinking{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.94,1:25:16.69,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎为了利益牺牲一切的信仰\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}based on this religion of profit at all costs,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.77,1:25:20.15,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎指望每个 ‎只顾自己私利的公司会突然神奇地\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}as if somehow, magically, each corporation acting in its selfish interest{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.24,1:25:21.95,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎去产生最好的结果\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}is going to produce the best result.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.03,1:25:24.49,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这已经影响环境很久了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}This has been affecting the environment for a long time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.57,1:25:27.28,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎恐怖的是 希望这是 ‎压倒骆驼的最后一根稻草\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}What's frightening, and what hopefully is the last straw{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.37,1:25:29.20,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎让我们作为文明的种族 去幡然醒悟\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}that will make us wake up as a civilization{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.29,1:25:31.70,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这个理论最初就有很多缺点\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}to how flawed this theory has been in the first place{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.79,1:25:35.00,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎让我们看到 我们现在就是树 就是鲸\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}is to see that now we're the tree, we're the whale.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.08,1:25:37.04,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们的关注就是被挖掘的矿产\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Our attention can be mined.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.13,1:25:39.13,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎如果我们花时间盯着一个屏幕\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We are more profitable to a corporation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.21,1:25:41.59,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎盯着一个广告 对公司而言\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}if we're spending time staring at a screen,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.67,1:25:42.97,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎比我们用这个时间\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}staring at an ad,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.05,1:25:45.89,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎过自己丰富的生活 更加有利可图\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}than if we're spending that time living our life in a rich way.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.97,1:25:47.55,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们看到了这样的后果\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And so, we're seeing the results of that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.64,1:25:50.68,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们看到公司利用强大的人工智能\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We're seeing corporations using powerful artificial intelligence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.77,1:25:53.52,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎凌驾在我们的智能之上 ‎研究怎样拉拢我们的关注\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}to outsmart us and figure out how to pull our attention{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.60,1:25:55.35,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎让我们去看 他们想让我们看的东西\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}toward the things they want us to look at,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.44,1:25:57.27,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎而不是让我们看 ‎与我们目标、价值观\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}rather than the things that are most consistent{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.36,1:25:59.23,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎与我们的生活最为一致的东西\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}with our goals and our values and our lives.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.99,1:26:04.45,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,{\an8}‎（史蒂夫·乔布斯 今日演讲者）\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}\N{\r\an8}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.53,1:26:06.91,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎电脑对我来说 是…\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}What a computer is,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.99,1:26:10.29,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎是我们人类历史上 最神奇的发明\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}is it's the most remarkable tool that we've ever come up with.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.12,1:26:13.87,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎相当于是我们思想的自行车\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And it's the equivalent of a bicycle for our minds.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.62,1:26:20.09,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎人道技术的创想 是硅谷最初的目标\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The idea of humane technology, that's where Silicon Valley got its start.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.05,1:26:25.72,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们已经背离了这个目标 ‎因为这样做比较酷\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And we've lost sight of it because it became the cool thing to do,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.80,1:26:27.26,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎而不是这样做比较正确\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}as opposed to the right thing to do.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.34,1:26:29.72,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎网络就是一个奇怪的、可笑的地方\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The Internet was, like, a weird, wacky place.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.80,1:26:31.39,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎它是实验性的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It was experimental.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.47,1:26:34.73,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎网络上发生着有创意的事情 ‎当然现在也有发生\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Creative things happened on the Internet, and certainly, they do still,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.81,1:26:38.61,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎但是感觉像一个巨大的商场\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}but, like, it just feels like this, like, giant mall.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.69,1:26:41.54,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎就是“天啊\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You know, it's just like, "God, there's gotta be...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.54,1:26:44.15,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎肯定不止表面上这么简单”\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}there's gotta be more to it than that."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.74,1:26:48.41,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我想我只是一个乐观主义者\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I guess I'm just an optimist.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.49,1:26:52.04,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎因为我认为 ‎我们可以改变社交媒体的样子和方式\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}'Cause I think we can change what social media looks like and means.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.08,1:26:56.76,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎技术的工作方式不是物理学定律\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The way the technology works is not a law of physics.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.76,1:26:58.00,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎它不是一成不变的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It is not set in stone.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.00,1:27:02.17,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这些都是像我这样的人类 ‎做出的选择\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}These are choices that human beings like myself have been making.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.75,1:27:05.34,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎人类可以改变这些技术\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And human beings can change those technologies.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.97,1:27:09.97,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎现在的问题是 我们是否愿意承认\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And the question now is whether or not we're willing to admit{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.47,1:27:15.43,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这些后果 是我们杰作的直接产物\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}that those bad outcomes are coming directly as a product of our work.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.02,1:27:24.86,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎这些东西是我们建立起来的 ‎我们有责任去改变它们\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's that we built these things, and we have a responsibility to change it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.21,1:27:38.79,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎提取关注模型\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The attention extraction model{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.79,1:27:42.29,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎不是我们想对待人类的方式\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}is not how we want to treat human beings.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.09,1:27:48.13,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎只有我这样想吗？还是…\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Is it just me or...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.84,1:27:50.84,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎可悲的人\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Poor sucker.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.51,1:27:53.22,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎一个健康社会的结构\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The fabric of a healthy society{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.30,1:27:56.14,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎要依靠我们脱离这种 ‎有破坏性的商业模型\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}depends on us getting off this corrosive business model.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.69,1:28:07.78,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们可以要求 ‎这些产品进行人道设计\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We can demand that these products be designed humanely.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.40,1:28:13.12,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们可以要求 ‎不被当做可以提取的资源对待\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We can demand to not be treated as an extractable resource.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.16,1:28:18.33,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎我们的动机可以是 ‎“我们怎样让这个世界变得更好？”\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The intention could be: "How do we make the world better?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.46,1:28:21.58,M - RYANLAUN,,0,0,0,,‎在整个人类历史中\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Throughout history,{\r}
